Overfitting anf Underfitting in KNN

cgpa| iq| placed : have data for 200 students , if k=1 , then the querys class will be the nearest neighbours class. Sometimes the query pointmustbe in blue but since its nearest point is pink it might be predicted as pink. 
Overfitting : data has high variance , different o/p on different data .


Underfitting: what is the max value of k = max val of n =200 , k=200 , and we get a query point and consider the 200 nearesit neighbours and then our whole data is considered, then the o/p will be the data which is dominated. of which has more no of data points either bl
blue or pink. 

K= low --> Overfitting
K= high -> Underfitting

Need to find intermediate value through experimentation 


Limitations of KNN:

Failure cases:
-> When we have lage datasets. n=5 lakh and features =100
   KNN is a lazy leanring technique , during traning no work and all work at prediction phase.

-> High dimensional data : Features =500 , curse of dimensionality , distance concept is not reliable.

-> KNN doesnt work well with outliers

-> Non homogenous scales : different units of measurements : one feature dominates the other then while calculating distance its not reliale

-> Imbalanced dataset : When only 1 o/p data points are dominated and biased

-> Using KNN for inference and not for prediction :  it acts like a black box model , it can say which feature is more important to predict the output









































































 
